1. Fix the "Mutual Payment Deadlock" (Monetization)
The Flaw: In Phase 4/5, both users must pay (e.g., $1) to unlock the chat. If User A pays, but User B ignores the request, User A feels scammed and will never pay again.
The Fix: Implement a Financial Escrow/Credit System.

When User A initiates the unlock, their $1 is authorized (or charged as a credit).

User B gets a notification: "Sam just paid to unlock your contact! Pay ₹99 to accept."

If User B doesn’t pay within 48 hours, User A gets an automatic refund or a "Free Unlock Token" for their next match. This completely removes the purchase hesitation for the first mover.

    2. Upgrade to "Hybrid Search" (Match Feed)
    The Flaw: In Phase 1 & 2, you generate a 1536-dimensional embedding and rely on that for the feed. Pure vector search (pgvector cosine similarity) is great for "vibes" and bio similarities, but it notoriously fails at strict constraints. It might match a 22-year-old with a 45-year-old just because they both wrote passionately about hiking.
    The Fix: Use a Hybrid Search Pipeline.

    First, use standard Postgres SQL filtering for non-negotiable dealbreakers (e.g., Age range, Religion, Diet, Location radius).

    Then, apply the pgvector semantic search only on the pool of candidates that survived the hard filters. This guarantees matches are both logistically viable and emotionally compatible.

3. Make PII Redactions Actionable (AI Escrow)
The Flaw: In Phase 4, the send-escrow-message intercepts and redacts PII. A flat blocked message frustrates users.
The Fix: Turn the AI Interceptor into a sales agent.

When the LLM detects a phone number, it shouldn't just replace it with [Redacted].

It should replace it with an interactive UI component in the chat: [Phone Number Hidden] -> Tap here to send a Mutual Unlock Request. Convert the friction directly into a monetization trigger.

4. SLA Grace Periods (Anti-Ghosting)
The Flaw: A strict 24-hour SLA (Phase 3) is brilliant for momentum, but humans have lives. If they match on a Friday night, they might not check the app until Sunday, resulting in a false "ghosted" status and an annoyed user.
The Fix: Add a "Snooze" or "Weekend Mode".

Allow users to toggle a "Busy" status that automatically pauses active SLAs.

Alternatively, extend the SLA to 48 hours for weekend matches, or let the sender trigger one "SLA Extension" nudge if they really like the person, before the AI Broker call kicks in.

5. The "Soft Pass" (Discovery)
The Flaw: Swiping left triggers Reject_Profile_RPC and sets the status to rejected. In matrimony, a "no" today might be a "yes" in 3 months if the user broadens their filters.
The Fix: Implement a "Maybe" or "Bookmark" state alongside the hard reject.

If they swipe left quickly, it's a soft pass (hide for 30 days).

If they explicitly block or hard-reject, it's permanent. This keeps your candidate pool from drying up too quickly in smaller cities.

